page.title: 12THE RECTOR HUSBANDS BOSWORTH
page.content: The rector of Husbands Bosworth in 1985 is Rev.Paul Collins.He arrived in 1983,the week after Easter.The Rector before was Ruggles Fisher, he retired six months before Mr Collins came. Mr Collins has been a rector for 10 years He likes his job except filling in forms.He came from Leicester where he had a very big parish.He holds four services a week.The earliest service is at 8.45 and it is in Theddingworth. The Rector is in charge of four parishes.They are Husbands Bosworth, Theddingworth,Mowsley and the Hamlet of Knaptoft.
